---

<section class="py-24 px-6 bg-gradient-to-b from-transparent via-red-950/20 to-transparent border-y border-red-900/30">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto space-y-12">
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1 bg-red-500/10 border border-red-500/40 rounded-full text-sm text-red-400">
        <span>⚠</span>
        <span>THE PROBLEM</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-5xl font-black">Merge conflicts in Markdown</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-400">
        Multiple developers editing the same large <code class="bg-gray-800 px-2 py-1 rounded text-red-300">CLAUDE.md</code> or <code class="bg-gray-800 px-2 py-1 rounded text-red-300">AGENTS.md</code> file creates semantic merge conflicts that are slow to resolve.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-center animate-on-scroll">
      <!-- Left: Problem description -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          When multiple developers edit the same agent instruction file, you hit merge conflicts. But these aren't simple syntax errors — they're <strong>semantic conflicts</strong> in instruction logic.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          Resolving them requires understanding the instruction intent, which is:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-400 font-bold">✗</span>
            <span>Slow — manual review of competing instruction versions</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-400 font-bold">✗</span>
            <span>Error-prone — easy to accidentally merge wrong intent</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-400 font-bold">✗</span>
            <span>Frustrating — happens repeatedly in large teams</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: Conflict code block -->
      <div class="bg-red-950/40 border border-red-900/50 rounded-xl p-6 overflow-x-auto font-mono text-sm font-medium">
        <div class="text-red-400 mb-3">← CONFLICT →</div>
        <pre class="text-gray-300"><code><span class="text-red-500">&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt; HEAD</span>
Your role is to be
a senior architect
focused on systems
design and patterns.
<span class="text-yellow-500">=======</span>
You are a Python
code reviewer who
catches bugs and
performance issues.
<span class="text-red-500">&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; branch</span></code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
